[
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's understand the statutory bookings first",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            119,
            558,
            136
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In company P, booking (1) shows there is a profit (financial income) for 320 corresponding to the  \\(80\\%\\)  of the gross dividends of 400 proposed by A. But A pays also 0.2 per each new share, so  \\(40 = 0.2^{*}200\\)  which represents a cash payment (Other assets).",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            151,
            890,
            217
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The total of  \\(360 = 320 + 40\\)  is booked as a debit on the financial investment.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            231,
            875,
            248
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In company A booking (2) shows the  \\(80 = 20\\%\\)  * 400 cash paid to  \\(3^{rd}\\)  Parties as dividends.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            263,
            886,
            298
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Booking (3) shows that the dividends for company A, that is  \\(320 = 80\\%\\)  400, are transferred from Reserves account to Capital account.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            310,
            886,
            344
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Booking (4) is related to the additional payment of 40 which is considered as a Share premium. We could also book it on the Capital account and it would make no difference from a consolidation point of view.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            360,
            888,
            410
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "There are also consolidation adjustments to book in company P",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            425,
            740,
            441
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (a) eliminates the financial income corresponding to the dividends for an amount of 320, just as we would do for normal dividends as discussed in Part 2.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            456,
            888,
            506
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (b) needs some explanations because of a percentage variation.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            521,
            862,
            539
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The approach we apply works perfectly well each time there is such variation.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            553,
            877,
            572
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "First we calculate the group equity before the transaction, that is",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            586,
            755,
            603
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n\\[\n80 \\% * [ 1000 + 800 + (200) + (400) ] = 960\n\\]\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            276,
            617,
            725,
            636
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "As equity, we consider Year 1 closing equity which is decreased by the 400 dividends that are processed separately.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            650,
            886,
            684
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Then we calculate the same group equity after the transaction",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            699,
            730,
            717
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n\\[\n83.33\\% * [1320 + 40 + 600 + (400)] = 1300\n\\]\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            269,
            730,
            730,
            749
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "giving an increase of  \\(340 = 1300 - 960\\)",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            764,
            513,
            780
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Of course, the financial investment in P on A has been increased by 360.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            796,
            826,
            812
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's go back to the logic of a normal company acquisition where we compare the price to acquire and the group equity, which gives a goodwill or a badwill.",
        "bbox": [
            113,
            827,
            886,
            863
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            115,
            64,
            374,
            81
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In this case, we have a goodwill for 20.",
        "bbox": [
            92,
            119,
            483,
            135
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (c): Decision has been taken to fully book this goodwill on P&L, because of low materiality.",
        "bbox": [
            92,
            150,
            871,
            185
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are now the consolidated accounts",
        "bbox": [
            94,
            200,
            492,
            215
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/f7257f38da02390f86a2a4b6e8d7919fb4280f04acbe26f5dffca70ec2293caf.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"3\">P + A</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves</td><td>1,520</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result</td><td>60</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Conso. Res.(A)</td><td>(957)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Minority int.(A)</td><td>277</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>8,000</td><td>Other liabilities</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            231,
            241,
            738,
            360
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where",
        "bbox": [
            96,
            378,
            162,
            391
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Consolidated reserves (A) = (957) = 83.33% * [1320 + 40 + 200 + 100] - [2000 + 360 + (20)]",
            "Minority interests (A)  \\(= 277 = 16.67\\%\\)  \\* [1320 + 40 + 200 + 100]"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            134,
            407,
            869,
            475
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In such consolidation, we recommend to justify at least the evolution of both group reserves and minority interests.",
        "bbox": [
            96,
            491,
            871,
            524
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Group reserves evolution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            96,
            540,
            349,
            555
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We show the justification report hereunder whose content comes immediately from the consolidated figures above.",
        "bbox": [
            96,
            571,
            871,
            605
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/6ab881ca316e3863f1c3783e140a394285df42d372075293e44bb07134fa88d4.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1 reserves</td><td>Year 2 result</td><td>Dividends</td><td>Dividends +</td><td>Dividends P</td><td>Year 2 reserves</td></tr><tr><td>P</td><td>1,500</td><td>60</td><td></td><td>320</td><td>(300)</td><td>1,580</td></tr><tr><td>A</td><td>(720)</td><td>83</td><td>(320)</td><td></td><td></td><td>(957)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>780</td><td>143</td><td>(320)</td><td>320</td><td>(300)</td><td>623</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            100,
            617,
            817,
            692
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Maybe just one comment: parent company P pays dividends for 300 to their shareholders. This information can be found in its statutory accounts.",
        "bbox": [
            96,
            708,
            871,
            742
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Minority interests evolution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            96,
            756,
            370,
            771
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here is the report",
        "bbox": [
            96,
            789,
            278,
            805
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 4 SPECIAL CONSOLIDATION TOPICS",
        "bbox": [
            432,
            70,
            854,
            85
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/b2fd8e094057951b5f524ad2a6d523c652485d3a8e2061540237ed443a2b153e.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1 reserves</td><td>Year 2 result</td><td>Dividends -</td><td>% var(1)</td><td>% var(2)</td><td>Year 2 reserves</td></tr><tr><td>A</td><td>320</td><td>17</td><td>(80)</td><td>(40)</td><td>60</td><td>277</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>320</td><td>17</td><td>(80)</td><td>(40)</td><td>60</td><td>277</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            115,
            828,
            177
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "which requires some additional comments for the  \\(0 \\%\\) var\" columns, the other columns not needing comments.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            192,
            883,
            225
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\\(\\%\\)  var(1) shows the variation of  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties percentage in the opening equity of Year 2 as",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            240,
            883,
            272
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n\\[\n(40) = [ 16.67 \\% - 20 \\% ] * [ 1000 + 800 + (200) + (400) ]\n\\]\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            218,
            288,
            781,
            307
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\\(\\%\\)  var(2) shows the  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties interests in the capital increase as",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            319,
            756,
            338
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n\\[\n60 = 16.67\\% * [320 + 40]\n\\]\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            364,
            351,
            635,
            370
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Notice that  \\(20 = (40) + 60\\)  is the goodwill recognized in the consolidation.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            384,
            841,
            403
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "But why do we have a goodwill on such capital increase? Was it expected?",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            417,
            841,
            434
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This goodwill is a consequence of the additional price which should have been a refund of 80 instead of a payment of 40.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            448,
            883,
            483
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Before the transaction, we have seen that the equity was 1200 for 1000 shares issued, so 1.2 per share.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            497,
            883,
            530
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The transaction itself concerns 200 shares for a value of  \\(360 = 320 + 40\\) , which gives a value of 1.8 per share. If, above the dividend of 320, company A would have refund 80, the value of one new share would have been  \\(1.2 = (320 - 80) / 200\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            545,
            881,
            611
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Finally, on this revisited basis, the total equity becomes  \\(1440 = 1200 + 240\\)  for 1200 shares, existing and new, giving a value of  \\(1.2 = 1440 / 1200\\)  per share equal to the value of a share before the transaction.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            624,
            883,
            675
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "2.3 Dividends paid on the basis of different types of shares representing the capital",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            118,
            711,
            819,
            756
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "When increasing its capital, a company can decide to issue new shares with special dividends. The capital is then represented by different categories of shares.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            760,
            883,
            810
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "If the basic rules of consolidation apply to such dividends when eliminating them, the percentage owned by the shareholders may be different in each",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            824,
            883,
            857
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            64,
            375,
            80
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "shares category which means that the part of result becomes more difficult to calculate.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            120,
            864,
            153
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's explain this with the following case study.",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            168,
            559,
            185
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Description of a situation",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            101,
            200,
            379,
            216
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We suppose parent company  \\(P\\)  is creating a new company  \\(A\\)  at the beginning of Year 1. Its capital is represented by two different categories of shares as shown hereunder, each share having a value of 1.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            232,
            867,
            282
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/52ed281a6272940bfa0c4073a2a4ce21d2bd33c9c39f92bd2d41f52435104098.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Shareholders</td><td>Parent</td><td>3rd Parties</td></tr><tr><td>Ordinary shares</td><td>1,000</td><td>200</td><td>800</td></tr><tr><td>Privileged shares</td><td>1,000</td><td>1,000</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>Total</td><td>2,000</td><td>1,200</td><td>800</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Net percentage</td><td>60%</td><td>40%</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            238,
            294,
            774,
            377
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Shares of each category have voting rights.",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            393,
            525,
            411
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The specific situation is that company A will pay each year dividends equal to  \\(5\\%\\)  of the corresponding capital of 1000, so 50. If for cash reasons, company A is not able to pay these dividends at the end of a certain year, it is carried forward in a cumulative way and paid the next year.",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            424,
            864,
            491
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For the analysis of our case study, we will limit our view to only equity accounts and study the consolidated reserves evolution.",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            506,
            864,
            538
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The statutory accounts",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            103,
            554,
            358,
            569
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We can see that parent company  \\(P\\)  is paying dividends of 100 at the end of Year 1 and Year 2.",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            585,
            864,
            617
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/b51537f4fa79710bdc4bb349167e5f1c5175a52b794c55318218ece41965be47.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"></td><td colspan=\"3\">Parent company P</td><td colspan=\"3\">Company A</td></tr><tr><td>Year 1</td><td>Year 2</td><td>Year 3</td><td>Year 1</td><td>Year 2</td><td>Year 3</td></tr><tr><td>Capital</td><td>1,000</td><td>1,000</td><td>1,000</td><td>2,000</td><td>2,000</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>800</td><td>900</td><td>1,000</td><td>0</td><td>(100)</td><td>30</td></tr><tr><td>Result</td><td>200</td><td>200</td><td>300</td><td>(100)</td><td>300</td><td>150</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            122,
            633,
            818,
            718
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "At the end of Year 1, company A makes a loss and, of course, the ordinary shares will give no dividends.",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            734,
            864,
            767
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For the privileged shares, on the contrary, company A has no choice: a dividend of 50 must be paid to the shareholders. However, its cash situation being bad, these dividends will be paid at the end of Year 2 if the situation improves in the meantime.",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            781,
            864,
            847
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 4 SPECIAL CONSOLIDATION TOPICS",
        "bbox": [
            434,
            70,
            850,
            86
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "At the end of Year 2, company A is able to pay the 50 related to Year 1 and the dividends of 50 related to Year 2, both concerning the privileged shares. Moreover, A decides also to pay a dividend of 0.07 per ordinary shares, so 14 = 0.07 * 200 to A and 56 = 0.07 * 800 to the  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            120,
            885,
            185
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The financial investment on company A in parent company P accounts can be deducted from the above information as  \\(1200 = 200\\)  ordinary shares of value  \\(1 + 1000\\)  privileged shares of value 1.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            199,
            885,
            250
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidated equity = Year 1, Year 2 and Year 3",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            116,
            263,
            641,
            282
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Hereunder we present the consolidated equity and, on two lines, the group and the  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties result.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            297,
            885,
            330
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/5b80a7fce0c3116fee165f2ceb4c289c6a6e3c43f3506236e57592d77ffb2bbe.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1</td><td>Year 2</td><td>Year 3</td></tr><tr><td>Capital</td><td>1,000</td><td>1,000</td><td>1,000</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>800</td><td>900</td><td>1,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>114</td></tr><tr><td>Result</td><td>200</td><td>200</td><td>300</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>(114)</td></tr><tr><td>Consolidated reserves</td><td>(60)</td><td>120</td><td>108</td></tr><tr><td>Minority interests</td><td>760</td><td>880</td><td>872</td></tr><tr><td>Group result</td><td>140</td><td>380</td><td>276</td></tr><tr><td>3rd Parties result</td><td>(40)</td><td>120</td><td>60</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            252,
            338,
            807,
            503
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For Year 1",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            118,
            521,
            224,
            537
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Consolidated reserves  \\(= (60) = 60\\%\\)  [2000 + (100)] - 1200",
            "Minority interests  \\(= 760 = 40\\%\\)  [2000 + (100)]",
            "- Group result  \\(= {140} = {200} + {60}\\% {}^{ * }\\)  (100)",
            "-  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties result = (40) = 40% * (100)"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            154,
            550,
            809,
            666
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's notice that the consolidated reserves for this first year are equal to the group result in company A.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            680,
            881,
            715
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For Year 2",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            118,
            730,
            224,
            743
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Consolidated reserves = 120 = 60% * [ 2000 + (100) + 300] - 1200",
            "Minority interests  \\(= 880 = 40\\%\\)  [2000 + (100) + 300]",
            "- Group result  \\(= {380} = {200} + {60}\\%  * {300}\\)",
            "-  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties result = 120 = 40% * 300"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            154,
            759,
            870,
            872
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            65,
            372,
            81
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For Year 3",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            103,
            121,
            205,
            136
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "During this Year 3, parent company P receives the dividends of 50 attached to the privileged shares of Year 1 and Year 2 and a dividend of 14 attached to the ordinary shares.",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            152,
            866,
            202
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This financial income, for a total of 114, is eliminated in parent company P in the usual way.",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            216,
            866,
            250
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Consolidated reserves = 108 = 60% * [2000 + 30 + 150] - 1200",
            "Minority interests  \\(= 872 = 40\\%\\)  [2000 + 30 + 150]",
            "- Group result  \\(= {276} = {300} + \\left( {114}\\right)  + {60}{\\% }^{ * }{150}\\)",
            "-  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties result = 60 = 40% * 150"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            139,
            265,
            709,
            377
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidated reserves evolution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            103,
            393,
            451,
            411
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Analyzing Year 2 with regard to Year 1, nothing special needs to be commented.",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            426,
            866,
            459
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/587a513b004075a602ad75a365fa2e1a5cd99eb14f8830f8c7d4fa289f693ede.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1\nreserves</td><td>Year 2\nresult</td><td>Dividends</td><td>Dividends</td><td>+ dividends</td><td>P</td><td>Year 2\nreserves</td></tr><tr><td>P</td><td>1,000</td><td>200</td><td></td><td></td><td>(100)</td><td>1,100</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>A</td><td>(60)</td><td>180</td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>120</td><td></td></tr><tr><td></td><td>940</td><td>380</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>(100)</td><td>1,220</td><td></td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            122,
            465,
            858,
            550
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "But when we do the same analysis for Year 3 with regard to Year 2, we get",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            565,
            836,
            582
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/bd0dc91bb1694c4ef257b42bf7efbd4068d6deae14523c9a7a23825098e88c86.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 2 reserves</td><td>Year 2 result</td><td>Dividends -</td><td>Dividends +</td><td>Dividends P</td><td>Year 3 reserves</td></tr><tr><td>P</td><td>1,100</td><td>186</td><td></td><td>114</td><td>(100)</td><td>1,300</td></tr><tr><td>A</td><td>120</td><td>90</td><td>(114)</td><td></td><td></td><td>108</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>1,220</td><td>276</td><td>(114)</td><td>114</td><td>(100)</td><td>1,408</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            120,
            595,
            858,
            680
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "showing a problem on the line corresponding to company A. An amount of 12 is not justified.",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            695,
            866,
            727
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This problem appears because we consolidate with a unique percentage of  \\(60\\%\\)  but in fact there are two percentages,  \\(20\\%\\)  and  \\(100\\%\\) , depending on the shares categories.",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            727,
            866,
            775
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In each consolidation, we systematically make a mistake on the group part in the result.",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            792,
            866,
            824
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The reserves and result of previous year contain the future dividends that are calculated as  \\(60\\%\\)  for the group. At the end of Year 2, the total dividends that",
        "bbox": [
            103,
            838,
            866,
            872
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 4 SPECIAL CONSOLIDATION TOPICS",
        "bbox": [
            436,
            73,
            853,
            87
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "will be paid is  \\(170 = 50 + 50 + 70\\)  and we consider  \\(102 = 60\\% * 170\\)  to be received by P.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            119,
            879,
            156
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The cash situation is different. The group receives  \\(114 = 50 + 50 + 20\\% * 70\\)  and the  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties receive in cash  \\(56 = 80\\% * 70\\)  instead of  \\(68 = 40\\% * 170\\)  as calculated in the consolidation process.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            169,
            879,
            220
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "So, the group should receive 12 more and the  \\(3^{rd}\\)  Parties 12 less and therefore the following consolidation adjustment needs to be booked in company A account.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            233,
            879,
            283
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/cdd0c84fe532c930df9803ef661a214be3320d44388edcef9db1581d27a7201d.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Debit</td><td>Credit</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>12</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Group result</td><td></td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>3rd Parties result</td><td>12</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Minority interests</td><td></td><td>12</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            308,
            307,
            704,
            391
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This adjustment impacts all accounts with  \\(100\\%\\)  of the amount.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            410,
            734,
            428
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Notice also that this adjustment has no impact on consolidated reserves and on minority interests, but only on the group result and the  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties result by applying a simple transfer for the amount of 12. No other accounts in the P&L are concerned by that adjustment.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            442,
            879,
            508
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Finally, the correct consolidated reserves evolution is the following",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            523,
            763,
            540
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/72dc4a51d76cdd7c0d9f31443418e66c8f3064080ab4b69b247de5291f9e2e9e.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 2 reserves</td><td>Year 2 result</td><td>Dividends -</td><td>Dividends +</td><td>Dividends P</td><td>Year 3 reserves</td></tr><tr><td>P</td><td>1,100</td><td>186</td><td></td><td>114</td><td>(100)</td><td>1,300</td></tr><tr><td>A</td><td>120</td><td>102</td><td>(114)</td><td></td><td></td><td>108</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>1,220</td><td>288</td><td>(114)</td><td>114</td><td>(100)</td><td>1,408</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            135,
            552,
            864,
            638
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Can this problem be avoided?",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            118,
            668,
            447,
            685
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Yes, indeed because each year, we calculate a wrong contribution to the result. The adjustment booked once dividends are paid could be booked preventively at the end of each consolidation.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            700,
            879,
            750
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            68,
            369,
            84
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "IN/OUT CONSOLIDATION SCOPE",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            219,
            120,
            778,
            144
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "3.1 Acquisition of a subgroup",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            99,
            163,
            580,
            188
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "On January 1, company P acquires  \\(60\\%\\)  of company A which owns subsidiary B. This company has been founded by company A a few years ago. In such situation, we say that company P acquires a subgroup.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            206,
            864,
            256
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "image",
        "img_path": "images/2562bdc1d153b1f4f2a223899d8fc068ee9ec4f129df6d96a3662f2412452571.jpg",
        "image_caption": [],
        "image_footnote": [],
        "bbox": [
            426,
            273,
            561,
            467
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "There are some important questions to consider before consolidating this subgroup for the first time",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            99,
            494,
            867,
            528
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Which accounts do we receive (or accept)? If A already consolidates since a number of years, it could indeed be interesting or easy to accept consolidated accounts for the subgroup A+B instead of consolidating individually these two new companies.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            544,
            864,
            609
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "If we integrate  \\(A + B\\)  consolidated accounts, are we sure the consolidation has been made with respect to the evaluation rules issued at company P level. P consolidation could be IFRS but not  \\(A + B\\) , or the opposite.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            623,
            864,
            674
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Supposing the evaluation rules are the same, there is a history in  \\(A + B\\) . Initial goodwill, revaluation of some assets, new provisions, translation adjustments, ... all booked through consolidation adjustments. Is it normal to take over all these adjustments in group P consolidation? Not sure at all!",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            688,
            864,
            754
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Moreover, we lose some transparency because the contribution in consolidated information will show A+B but not A and B individually.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            768,
            864,
            802
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "By consolidating that subgroup for the first time, the goodwill or badwill will be naturally calculated on  \\(A + B\\)  consolidated equity.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            816,
            864,
            850
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 4 SPECIAL CONSOLIDATION TOPICS",
        "bbox": [
            432,
            71,
            850,
            87
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "If there is a goodwill, such a \"black box\" will make difficult to book an allocation of this goodwill on some assets in A which are consolidated with those of B.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            118,
            885,
            168
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A final question under this assumption is to know what could be the future of company B. If the interesting company for group P is A, company B could be disposed to  \\(3^{\\text{rd}}\\)  Parties in a short term. Integrating consolidated A+B figures should then be avoided.",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            183,
            885,
            247
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "If we consolidate individual accounts, goodwill/badwill calculated separately on A and B wouldn't be correct because there is a unique transaction to acquire a subgroup and not two companies.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            263,
            883,
            313
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Whether we consolidate companies A and B on a direct basis or not, with a unique goodwill/badwill, we would recommend to split the value on A and B in case company B is disposed and not A.",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            326,
            883,
            376
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A last comment concerns the possibility that company P acquires shares of company B, taking a direct participation. This would not be advisable, but we never now. Supposing we consolidate on the A+B consolidated basis, this new group structure would become difficult to manage because we would know the value of the financial investment from P into B without knowing the exact value of the equity of B, hidden in A+B.",
        "bbox": [
            116,
            392,
            885,
            489
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We will solve our case study by integrating separately companies A and B.",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            504,
            838,
            521
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjusted statutory accounts of each company",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            118,
            536,
            616,
            552
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's consider the statutory accounts already adjusted with the goodwill.",
        "bbox": [
            118,
            568,
            819,
            586
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/72197d674296e8eacf3d65688a5131cba08e96cceecfd146a30e79f0fa227e73.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"4\">P</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\">Goodwill</td><td rowspan=\"2\">(a) 102(b) 42</td><td>Capital</td><td>3,000</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>1,000</td></tr><tr><td>Fin. Inv./A</td><td>(a) 1,500(b) (102)(42)</td><td>Result</td><td>200</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>4,500</td><td>Other liabilities</td><td>1,800</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\">A</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"3\">Fin. Inv./B</td><td rowspan=\"3\">800</td><td>Capital</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>500</td></tr><tr><td>Result</td><td>100</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>4,200</td><td>Other liabilities</td><td>2,400</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            230,
            604,
            735,
            843
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            120,
            65,
            375,
            80
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/3427965fb597eff609ec7ba0e9f8a4756f9d9b9bcbccdf425dd5a394c04638af.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"3\">B</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital</td><td>1,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves</td><td>(300)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result</td><td>(100)</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>3,000</td><td>Other liabilities</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            216,
            115,
            720,
            200
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Goodwill calculation",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            99,
            215,
            326,
            231
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The goodwill is the difference between the acquisition price, 1500, and the consolidated equity of the subgroup.",
        "bbox": [
            97,
            247,
            868,
            280
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The calculation is detailed here.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            294,
            408,
            310
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This consolidated equity is calculated as in a normal consolidation of A and B, company A playing temporarily the role of a parent or consolidating company. Moreover, the equity to consider is the one as of January  \\(1^{st}\\) , so without the result of the year.",
        "bbox": [
            97,
            326,
            491,
            441
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/550107f3897864c2a8549e9929b9e6345700f374b4e11f72bf879395bc5b5a4f.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td>Acquisition price</td><td>1,500</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            504,
            291,
            860,
            315
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/fbc79a7fb388378638bf8d38dcaa4e7021ec715326dce25c394495b35f162e58.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td>Equity (A)</td><td>2,500</td></tr><tr><td>Consolidated reserves B</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>E uit A+B</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Grou-% ac.uired</td><td>60%</td></tr><tr><td>Grou e uit ac.uired</td><td></td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            504,
            328,
            860,
            413
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/1504e2e6dfc36476c1cbbe92882e41855f1d0fae35e29667e3e9e443f94195f6.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td>Goodwill</td><td>144</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            504,
            422,
            860,
            445
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For information, (240)  \\(= 80\\%\\)  \\* [1000 + (300)] - 800.",
        "bbox": [
            99,
            453,
            639,
            473
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This goodwill is then split into two parts, one related to A and one related to B in case of selling B separately. The criteria to use has to be proposed and accepted by the Auditors and, in our case, we would weight the goodwill according to the net equity of A and B as follows",
        "bbox": [
            97,
            488,
            866,
            552
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Opening net equity of  \\(A = 1700 = 2500 - 800\\)",
            "- Opening net equity of  \\(\\mathrm{B} = {700}\\)"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            139,
            568,
            633,
            617
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "giving a total net equity of 2400 and so",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            633,
            491,
            649
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "Goodwill attached to  \\(A = 102 = 144^*\\)  (1700/2400)",
            "Goodwill attached to  \\(\\mathsf{B} = 42 = 144^{\\star}\\)  (700/2400)"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            139,
            661,
            694,
            714
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "which explains consolidation adjustments (a) and (b).",
        "bbox": [
            101,
            728,
            625,
            747
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 4 SPECIAL CONSOLIDATION TOPICS",
        "bbox": [
            434,
            68,
            853,
            85
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    }
]